title: Configuration

The configuration settings are at the very top of the loader.js script. 

> Changing the config requires no experience in JavaScript!

```js
// Options
const opts = {
    mws: {
        port: '8200',
        host: '127.0.0.1',
        dir: './public/mws'
    },
    appdir: './public/wikis',
    expdir: './public/exports'
};

```

Edit `./loader.js` and will see port, host, and dir settings for Multi-Wiki-Server. The port is 8200 (instead of the default 8080) because it seems Everything! uses 8080 and will probably conflict with some other server - so using port 8200 by default.

host '127.0.0.1' (official address of 'localhost') runs the server on your local machine. Only a browser running on the same computer can access localhost.

